   <h1>ONE PIECE</h1>
   <p>The Straw Hat Pirates, also known as the Mugiwara Pirates,<br>
   Straw Hat Crew, or simply the Straw Hats, are an extremely infamous and </br>
   powerful pirate crew that originated from the East Blue.</p>
  <p class="redtext">Monkey D. Luffy, commonly known as "Straw Hat Luffy"</br>
   or simply "Straw Hat", is the founder, captain, and </br>
   strongest combatant <span>of the increasingly infamous and powerful </br>
   Straw Hat Pirates.</span> He fearlessly pursues the legendary </br>
   treasure of the late Gol D. Roger in order to become the new </br>
   Pirate King and reach a further, untold dream (currently known </br>
   to only his crew and closest friends).He believes that being </br>
   the Pirate King means having the most freedom in the world.</br>
   </p>
   <p class="whitetext">Born on Dawn Island, Luffy is the son of Revolutionary</br>
   leader Monkey D. Dragon[32] and grandson of the Marine hero</br>
   Monkey D. Garp[33] and as such is a carrier of the mysterious</br>
   "D" legacy. Most of his childhood was shaped by Garp and Curly </br>
   Dadan,[34] under whose care he befriended and swore brotherhood</br>
   to the late Portgas D. "Fire Fist" Ace[35] and Revolutionary officer</br>
   Sabo.[36] However, he draws his greatest inspiration from the pirate</br>
   "Red-Haired" Shanks, who (unwittingly) enabled him to eat the Devil Fruit</br>
   that turned his body into rubber,[37] sacrificed an arm to save his </br>
   life, and gifted his signature straw hat as a symbol of their vow to</br>
   reunite someday, after Luffy became a great pirate.</br>
   </br>
   <p id="roropara">Roronoa Zoro,also known as "Pirate Hunter" Zoro,</br>
   is a main combatant of the Straw Hat Pirates, one of their</br>
   two swordsmen, one of the Senior Officers of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet,</br>
   and is publicly recognized as the right-hand man of his crew's captain </br>
   Monkey D. Luffy.Formerly a bounty hunter, he is the second member </br>
   of Luffy's crew and the first to join it, doing so in the Romance Dawn Arc.</br>
   </p>
